data.name: startCountdown.ToolTip
data.value:
Images and a csv text file are saved in the temp folder within the TeboCam folder.
The text file can be imported into a spreadhseet to graph and analyse movement detection over time. (Note that files in the temp folder are deleted when TeboCam starts up)

data.name: trainVal.ToolTip
data.value:
The frequency, in seconds, at which to save images.
The recomended value is 0.5 The lowest value allowed is 0.25 (0.5 will save two images every second)

data.name: countVal.ToolTip
data.value:
The number of seconds to run the calibration test for.
The recommended value is 30.

data.name: linkLightSpike.Text
data.value: If you don't have a copy of the light spike detection manual - you can get a copy by clicking on this line
